# Tailwind Theming (BSI)

## Design tokens location
Primary tokens defined in `src/styles/tokens/`:
- `colors.ts` — Color palette
- `typography.ts` — Fonts, sizes, weights
- `spacing.ts` — Margin/padding scale
- `breakpoints.ts` — Responsive breakpoints

## Color system
```typescript
// Brand colors
brand: {
  primary: '#FF6B35',    // Blaze orange
  secondary: '#1A1A2E',  // Deep navy
  accent: '#F7931E',     // Gold
}

// Semantic colors
semantic: {
  success: '#10B981',    // Wins, positive stats
  warning: '#F59E0B',    // Watch, caution
  error: '#EF4444',      // Losses, negative
  info: '#3B82F6',       // Informational
}
```

## Usage rules
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — use semantic tokens
<div className="bg-brand-primary text-white">
<span className="text-semantic-success">

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded colors
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#FF6B35' }}>
<span className="text-green-500">  // Use semantic-success instead
```

## Responsive breakpoints
Mobile-first approach:
```tsx
// Base (mobile) → md (tablet) → lg (desktop) → xl (large)
<div className="p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">
```

## Typography scale
Use consistent text sizes:
- `text-xs` — Labels, metadata
- `text-sm` — Secondary text
- `text-base` — Body text
- `text-lg` — Subheadings
- `text-xl+` — Headings

## Extending the theme
When adding new tokens:
1. Add to appropriate `src/styles/tokens/*.ts`
2. Import in `tailwind.config.ts`
3. Document the new token's purpose
4. Never add one-off colors/values
